	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p><placeName>La Fayette</placeName> Inc <date>24 June 5617</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Revd &#38; Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My engagements are brief&#44;<lb/> &#38; so are yours&#59; allow me therefore<lb/> to ask of you an immediate reply<lb/> upon the following questions.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">1. Whether the <add>Hebrew</add> is not allowed to<lb/> Kill for a member of his Congren on<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> when called upon&#59; after he hath<lb/> prepared his <add>Hebrew</add> &#38;c <add>Hebrew</add> on <add>Hebrew</add>&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">2. Whether the <add>Hebrew</add> is bound to ask<lb/> the party that desire his services&#44; say&#44;<lb/> to kill an <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; whether it is for<lb/> a sick person&#63;  &#40;consequently&#44; if it<lb/> is not for a sick person he must<lb/> not kill it&#33;&#41;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">3. rdly <del>Whether the <add>Hebrew</add> has</del> Upon which day of <add>Hebrew</add> the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> has more permission&#44; according</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>to <add>Hebrew</add> &#38;c &#38;c<lb/> on the first or on the second&#63;<lb/>  I shall esteem it a particular favor&#44; if you have<lb/> the goodness in answering<lb/> me the above <sic>querries</sic><lb/> as soon as possible.</p>
				<p>It&#39;s most astonishing<lb/> how pious people &#40;that<lb/> violate the <date>Sabbath</date> &#38;c<lb/> &#38; defile the Law of <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> &#38;c. &#38; never enter the gate<lb/> of a Syn.&#41; are&#44; that when<lb/> they see that the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> hath Nulled a chicken<lb/> on the first day <add>Hebrew</add> for</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>a member&#59; they<lb/> <sic>challeng</sic> &#38; abuse<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> for being<lb/> very indifferent<lb/> to his duty&#33;  And<lb/> of cause&#44; who shall<lb/> decide upon such<lb/> matters&#63;  if I offer<lb/> them the <add>Hebrew</add> they<lb/> can&#39;t read&#8212;nor have<lb/> they faith in the translation<lb/> of a person so wicked<lb/> &#40;according to their <sic>oppinion</sic>&#41; as<lb/> to kill an <add>Hebrew</add> when <del>aft</del> demanded<lb/> of him&#33;  Yr kind answer<lb/> I will show to justify my&#61;<lb/>self.  Yrs faithfully</p>
				<p><persName role="author">H Lowenthal</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
				<p>N. B.</p>
				<p>Shall the <add>Hebrew</add> be<lb/> guided in his capacity<lb/> by <hi rend="underline">some</hi> of his con.<lb/> &#40;which seek their<lb/> destruction &#38; not<lb/> their welfare&#41; or by<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> appertaining<lb/> to <add>Hebrew</add> where<lb/> shall <hi rend="underline">he</hi> or <hi rend="underline">they</hi> seek<lb/> redress &#38; upon whose<lb/> judgment &#38;c ought they<lb/> to rely&#63;  A comment on the<lb/> above theme in yr next <sic>valle.</sic><lb/> magazine will be gratefully<lb/> admired.  <persName role="author">H. L.</persName></p>
		</body>
